Peter Jennings, the iconic ABC News anchor, revealed his battle with lung cancer, opting for chemotherapy over surgery.
Despite his illness, he remains committed to anchoring "World News Tonight" during treatment.
Colleagues and industry experts praise his dedication and impact on broadcast journalism.
Viewers express support and admiration for his openness about his health struggles.
The news of his absence from the newscast due to treatment has sparked discussions about his legacy and the future of network news.
Jennings' resilience and determination in the face of adversity inspire many.
